{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2024-2331","published":"2024-11-01T11:09:32Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:20:47.557164Z","upstream":["CVE-2024-9050"],"summary":"NetworkManager-libreswan security update","details":"This package provides easy connections to IPsec VPNs using NetworkManager and Libreswan.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nA flaw was found in the libreswan client plugin for NetworkManager (NetkworkManager-libreswan), where it fails to properly sanitize the VPN configuration from the local unprivileged user. In this configuration, composed by a key-value format, the plugin fails to escape special characters, leading the application to interpret values as keys. One of the most critical parameters that could be abused by a malicious user is the `leftupdown`key. This key takes an executable command as a value and is used to specify what executes as a callback in NetworkManager-libreswan to retrieve configuration settings back to NetworkManager. As NetworkManager uses Polkit to allow an unprivileged user to control the system&apos;s network configuration, a malicious actor could achieve local privilege escalation and potential code execution as root in the targeted machine.(CVE-2024-9050)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"NetworkManager-libreswan","ecosystem":"openEuler:22.03-LTS-SP1","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/NetworkManager-libreswan&distro=openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP1"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"1.2.24-1.oe2203sp1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["NetworkManager-libreswan-1.2.24-1.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm","NetworkManager-libreswan-debuginfo-1.2.24-1.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm","NetworkManager-libreswan-debugsource-1.2.24-1.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm","NetworkManager-libreswan-gnome-1.2.24-1.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm"],"src":["NetworkManager-libreswan-1.2.24-1.oe2203sp1.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["NetworkManager-libreswan-1.2.24-1.oe2203sp1.x86_64.rpm","NetworkManager-libreswan-debuginfo-1.2.24-1.oe2203sp1.x86_64.rpm","NetworkManager-libr